  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "2021 A/L Practicals from today (19)",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "COLOMBO (News 1st); G. C. E. Advanced Level Practical Examinations for candidates who missed it in 2021 will commence on Friday (19), said the Department of Examinations.",
        "Commissioner General of Examinations L.M.D Dharmasena told that the relevant practical tests will be held on Saturday (20) and Sunday (21) as well.",
        "Dharmasena said that due to the fuel crisis and problematic conditions, students were unable to appear for the practical tests.",
        "He said that the relevant examinations will be completed and the Advanced Level examination results will be released in two weeks.",
        "Meanwhile, Commissioner General of Examination L.M.D Dharmasena announced that the third phase of the evaluation of the answer sheets of the G.C.E Ordinary Level Examination will begin tomorrow (20).",
        "The deadline for accepting applications for the 2022 G.C.E Advanced Level Examination has been extended to the 26th of August.",
        "Pohottuwa wants Gotabaya back in Sri Lanka with security, and facilities"
      ],
